The paper deals with the computational complexity of a problem related to Boolean polynomials, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The problem involves counting the number of zeroes and ones of a polynomial, which is related to algorithms for counting and enumeration (cs.DS, cs.DM). The paper also uses techniques from quantum computation (cs.QC) and promises a PP-completeness result, which is related to the study of complexity classes (cs.SC).
